2016/snapshot-pete-barresi/</ref><ref>https://ballotpedia.org/Peter_Robert_Barresi</ref>\n* [[Robert F. Hyde]], [[U.S. Marine Corps]] veteran<ref>{{cite web|url=https://hydeforcongress.com/|title=Hyde for Congress|accessdate=December 14, 2019}}</ref>\n*Ryan Meehan, businessman and military veteran<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.middletownpress.com/middletown/article/Exclusive-Another-Republican-joins-5th-District-14951820.php|title=Exclusive: Another Republican joins 5th District race|first=Emilie|last=Munson|date=January 6, 2020|website=The Middletown Press}}</ref>\n* Ruben Rodriguez, former [[Waterbury, Connecticut|Waterbury]] city plan commissioner and candidate for the [[Connecticut House of Representatives]] in 2014<ref name=CT2020>{{Cite news|last1=Radelat|first1=Ana|title=CT Dems attracting early GOP challenges|url=https://ctmirror.org/2019/07/10/ct-dems-attracting-early-gop-challenges|website=The CT Mirror|date=July 10, 2019|accessdate=August 29, 2019}}</ref><ref>https://ballotpedia.org/Ruben_Rodriguez</ref>\n* David X. Sullivan, former assistant U.S. Attorney<ref>{{cite news|last1=Matarazzo Jr.|first1=Bruno|title=Former federal prosecutor from New Fairfield seeking Republican nomination for 5th Congressional District|url=https://www.rep-am.com/local/news-local/2019/07/02/former-federal-prosecutor-from-new-fairfield-seeking-republican-nomination-for-5th-congressional-district/|newspaper=Republican-American|date=July 2, 2019|accessdate=July 3, 2019}}</ref>\n\n====Primary Results====\n{{Election box begin no change\n|title = Republican primary results\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = Pete Barresi\n| party = Republican Party (United States)\n| votes = \n| percentage = \n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = [[Robert F. Hyde]]\n| party = Republican Party (United States)\n| votes = \n| percentage = \n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = Ryan Meehan\n| party = Re